Argentine Stocks: Banco Macro, Banco Hipotecario, Pampa Energia

-- B y   C a m i l a   R u s s o
-- 
2011-06-16T16:53:20Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-16/argentine-stocks-banco-macro-banco-hipotecario-pampa-energia.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in Argentine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 12:29 p.m. New York time.  The Merval Index fell 0.5 percent to 3,229.13.  Banks dropped in line with global financial companies after
Greek Prime Minister  George Papandreou  said he will reshuffle
his cabinet and seek a confidence vote.  Banco Macro SA (BMA)  ,  Argentina ’s largest lender by
market value, declined 1 percent to 14.85 pesos.  Banco
Hipotecario SA (BHIP)   retreated 0.5 percent to 2.21 pesos.  Energy companies fell after President  Cristina Fernandez de
Kirchner  said economic growth will slow to 7.5 percent this year
from 9.2 percent last year.  Pampa Energia SA (PAMP)  , Argentina’s largest power
generator, fell 0.8 percent to 2.57 pesos. Cia. De Transporte de
Energia Electrica en Alta Tension Transener SA (TRAN AF), a
power transmission company, lost 0.7 percent to 1.41 pesos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Camila Russo in New York at 
 crusso15@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
